{"parse":{"title":"Abu Bakr al-Ajurri","pageid":45677009,"revid":799599330,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size: 130%;\"><span class=\"fn\">al-Ajurri<br />\u0627\u0644\u0622\u062c\u064f\u0631\u0650\u0651\u064a</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\nImam</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<span class=\"birthplace\"><a href=\"/wiki/Baghdad\" title=\"Baghdad\">Baghdad</a>, Iraq</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n970 / 320 <a href=\"/wiki/Hijri_year\" title=\"Hijri year\">AH</a><br /><span class=\"deathplace\"><a href=\"/wiki/Mecca\" title=\"Mecca\">Mecca</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Hejaz\" title=\"Hejaz\">Hejaz</a></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Religion</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Islam\" title=\"Islam\">Islam</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Denomination</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Sunni\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sunni\">Sunni</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Jurisprudence</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Shafi%27i\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shafi&#39;i\">Shafi'i</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Hanbali\" title=\"Hanbali\">Hanbali</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<b><a href=\"/wiki/Arabic_name\" title=\"Arabic name\">Arabic name</a></b></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.4em; line-height:135%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Ism_(name)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ism (name)\">Personal&#32;<small>(<i>Ism</i>)</small></a></th><td>\nMu\u1e25ammad<br />\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.4em; line-height:135%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Nasab\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nasab\">Patronymic&#32;<small>(<i>Nasab</i>)</small></a></th><td>\nibn al-\u1e24usayn ibn \u02bfAbdall\u0101h;<br />\u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.4em; line-height:135%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Kunya_(Arabic)\" title=\"Kunya (Arabic)\">Teknonymic&#32;<small>(<i>Kunya</i>)</small></a></th><td>\nAb\u016b Bakr<br />\u0623\u0628\u0648 \u0628\u0643\u0631</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.4em; line-height:135%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Nisba_(onomastics)\" title=\"Nisba (onomastics)\">Toponymic&#32;<small>(<i>Nisba</i>)</small></a></th><td>\nal-\u0100jurr\u012b; Al-<a href=\"/wiki/Baghdad\" title=\"Baghdad\">Baghdadi</a>;</td></tr><tr style=\"display:none\"><td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Imam al-Ajurri</b> was an Islamic scholar from 10th century (4th century <a href=\"/wiki/Hijri_year\" title=\"Hijri year\">AH</a>). He came from Darb al-Ajurr in western <a href=\"/wiki/Baghdad\" title=\"Baghdad\">Baghdad</a>, after studying with many scholar in Iraq he moved to <a href=\"/wiki/Mecca\" title=\"Mecca\">Mecca</a> and start teaching there. He lived in Mecca for 30 years until he died there in 970 / 320 AH.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Al-Ajurri commonly known as Shafi'is scholar, while Ibn Abi Ya'la stated he is a Hanbalis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Among his teacher is Al-Hafiz Abul Muslim Ibrahim bin Abdillah bin Muslim <a href=\"/wiki/Basra\" title=\"Basra\">Al-Bashri</a> Al-Kajji (d.292 H) and also Abu Bakr Abd-allah bin Sulayman bin Al-Ash\u2019ath <a href=\"/wiki/Sistan\" title=\"Sistan\">As-Sijistani</a> (d.316 H) one of sheikh in Baghdad, the son of Imam <a href=\"/wiki/Abu_Dawud\" title=\"Abu Dawud\">Abu Dawud</a> of Sunan Abu Dawud.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> While one of his famous student is <a href=\"/wiki/Abu_Nu%60aym\" title=\"Abu Nu`aym\">Abu Nu'aym al-Asbahani</a> who transmitted hadith from him.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"His_Writings\">His Writings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Abu_Bakr_al-Ajurri&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: His Writings\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Al-Ajurri wrote many books, even many of them were lost, some surviving work still published today. Some of his writing are:\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://ar.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8_%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B9%D8%A9\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"ar:\u0643\u062a\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0631\u064a\u0639\u0629\">Kit\u0101b al-Shar\u012b\u02bbah</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/38959587\">38959587</a> One of his important book.</li>\n<li>Akhl\u0101q al-\u02bbulam\u0101\u02bc <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/18820407\">18820407</a></li>\n<li>Kit\u0101b al-arba\u02bb\u012bn \u1e25ad\u012bthan <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/25461361\">25461361</a></li>\n<li>Akhl\u0101q \u1e25amalat al-Qur\u02bc\u0101n <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/22987732\">22987732</a></li>\n<li>Akhl\u0101q ahl al-Qur\u02bc\u0101n <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/23483970\">23483970</a></li>\n<li>Kit\u0101b al-ta\u1e63d\u012bq bi-al-na\u1e93ar il\u00e1 All\u0101h ta\u02bb\u0101l\u00e1 f\u012b al-\u0101khirah <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/23141885\">23141885</a></li>\n<li>Ta\u1e25r\u012bm al-nard wa-al-shi\u1e6dranj wa-al-mal\u0101h\u012b <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/23178546\">23178546</a></li>\n<li>Akhb\u0101r Ab\u012b \u1e24af\u1e63 \u02bbUmar ibn \u02bbAbd al-\u02bbAz\u012bz wa-s\u012bratuh <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/50195268\">50195268</a></li>\n<li>Dhamm al-liw\u0101\u1e6d <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/33854700\">33854700</a>,</li>\n<li>Kit\u0101b al-ghurab\u0101\u02bc<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/48871474\">48871474</a>, etc.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Acknowledgment\">Acknowledgment</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Abu_Bakr_al-Ajurri&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Acknowledgment\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Ibn_Khallikan\" title=\"Ibn Khallikan\">Ibn Khallikan</a> says:\"He was Shafi'i jurist and a muhaddith, he is the author of famous book Al-Arba'in. He was a righteous and pious man.\"\n<a href=\"/wiki/Al-Dhahabi\" title=\"Al-Dhahabi\">Al-Dhahabi</a> says:\" The Imam, the Muhaddith, he was the Imam of the grand Mosque in Makkah (Imam al-Haram); a truthful, charitable and a pious man, a man of exemplary character.\"\n<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=As-Subki&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"As-Subki (page does not exist)\">As-Subki</a> says: \"(He is a) Jurist, muhaddith, have many works.\"\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Abu_Bakr_al-Ajurri&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://islamcivil.ru/biografiya-imama-abu-bakra-al-adzhurri-um-360/\">\"Biografiya imama Abu bakra al-Adzhurri (um. 360)\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">15 March</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Biografiya+imama+Abu+bakra+al-Adzhurri+%28um.+360%29&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fislamcivil.ru%2Fbiografiya-imama-abu-bakra-al-adzhurri-um-360%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAbu+Bakr+al-Ajurri\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ibn_Abi_Ya%27la&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ibn Abi Ya&#39;la (page does not exist)\">Ibn Abi Ya'la</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Tabaqat_al-Hanabilah\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tabaqat al-Hanabilah\">Tabaqat al-Hanabilah</a> (pg. 332)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Su\u02bc\u0101l\u0101t Ab\u012b \u02bbUbayd al-\u0100jurr\u012b Ab\u0101 Da\u02bc\u016bd Sulaym\u0101n ibn al-Ash\u02bbath al-Sijist\u0101n\u012b (202-275 H) f\u012b ma\u02bbrifat al-rij\u0101l wa-jar\u1e25ihim wa-ta\u02bbd\u012blihim</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<dl><dt>Bibliography</dt></dl>\n<ul><li>Al-Ajurri, Abu Bakr, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.scribd.com/doc/248037438/Abu-Bakr-Al-Ajurri-Kitab-Al-Sharia#scribd\">Kitab Ash-Shariah</a> pg.5</li></ul>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Muslim_scholars_of_the_Hanbali_School\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><